            text: "Compare this to Chapter 18, Verse 78, the final verse of the Gita, which states that wherever there is Krishna (the Master of Yoga) and Arjuna (the archer), there will be victory, prosperity, and morality. This provides the 'final answer' to Duryodhana's counting of warriors in Chapter 1.",
