            title: "Ritual as Anchor",
            text: "Anthropologically, rituals like offering food to the dead provide psychological closure and continuity for the living. Arjuna is terrified of losing this psychological anchor. His fear of the ancestors 'falling' is actually his own fear of falling into a reality without comforting structures.",
