            title: "Kṛta-niścayaḥ (Firm Determination)",
            text: "This is the antidote to 'Dharma-sammūḍha' (confusion). Once the intellect recognizes that righteous action cannot fail conceptually, the mind must lock in. Niścaya means a resolved, unshakeable intellect. Action without Niścaya is weak; Niścaya without action is a daydream. Both must combine.",
