          title: "Work & Career",
          text: "If you only do your job for the Friday paycheck or the annual bonus, you are a professional 'Miser' (Kripana). You will hate Monday through Thursday. If you take refuge in the 'Buddhi' of your craft—focusing on excellence, service, and mastery—your entire work week becomes a rich, fulfilling experience.",
