          text: "The entire modern global economy is built on making you fail the first half of this verse. Advertising exists to plant 'kāmān' (desires) in your 'mano-gatān' (mind), convincing you that you are incomplete without a product. The Sthita-prajña is the ultimate rebel against consumerism, destroying the advertiser's power by being perfectly happy with nothing but their own breath and awareness.",
