          title: "Work & Career",
          text: "When a project fails (Duḥkha), the average professional panics. When it succeeds (Sukha), they become arrogant and crave a bigger bonus. The 'Muni' in the office stays totally calm during the failure, learns from it, and stays humble during the success, ready for the next task. They are the most dangerous and effective person in the room.",
