            text: "Whatever you practice during your life is what you will default to under the intense biological stress of death. If you practice greed and fear for 80 years, you will be consumed by greed and fear on your deathbed. To be in 'Brāhmī-sthiti' at the end requires cultivating that steady wisdom *now*. The verse is a promise of grace, not a loophole for lazy behavior.",
