            title: "Anasūyantaḥ (Without Envy/Cynicism)",
            text: "Asūyā is a toxic psychological state combining envy, fault-finding, and cynicism. It is the ego's defense mechanism against a superior truth. If a student listens to a master with 'Asūyā', they are not listening to learn; they are listening to find a flaw so they can maintain their own egoic superiority. The Truth cannot enter a cynical mind.",
