            title: "The Working Hypothesis",
            text: "Krishna explicitly encourages questioning (as seen throughout the Gita). Śraddhā does not mean 'stop thinking'; it means 'stop fighting the teaching long enough to actually try it.' It is the faith of a scientist running an experiment, trusting the scientific method until the results are proven.",
