            text: "Despite their beautiful faith, they are 'Ayati' (lacking the fierce, painful effort required). When the alarm goes off at 5 AM to meditate, their faith is strong, but their discipline is weak, so they go back to sleep. Consequently, the mind wanders back to material comforts (calita-mānasaḥ), and they die before reaching the finish line. What happens to the wasted potential?",
